					<description><![CDATA[On the subject of pubs closing (or indeed for many POIs), it would be useful to note how one would mark a pub closed - i.e. by following the &#039;disused:x&#039; lifecycle scheme.

Such that an amenity=pub -&#062; disused:amenity=pub

See http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Disused for further detail.

Perhaps someone might want to adjust the tags for an ex pub in your area very near to your example on the A3400 North out of Stratford-Upon-Avon ;)

http://www.openstreetmap.org/way/158021422]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>On the subject of pubs closing (or indeed for many POIs), it would be useful to note how one would mark a pub closed &#8211; i.e. by following the &#8216;disused:x&#8217; lifecycle scheme.</p>
<p>Such that an amenity=pub -&gt; disused:amenity=pub</p>
<p>See <a href="http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Disused" rel="nofollow ugc">http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Disused</a> for further detail.</p>
<p>Perhaps someone might want to adjust the tags for an ex pub in your area very near to your example on the A3400 North out of Stratford-Upon-Avon 😉</p>
<p><a href="http://www.openstreetmap.org/way/158021422" rel="nofollow ugc">http://www.openstreetmap.org/way/158021422</a></p>
